dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Finch c I Sharma b Yadav 107 (107b 9x4 2x6 153m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Ishant takes the catch from mid-on. Good length on off, Finch goes for the pull but the ball bounces and takes the outside half. The ball lobs up and Ishant runs around from mid-on, even as Kohli from midwicket was running back. Ishant keeps his eyes on the ball and hangs on comfortably. And then has a word with Kohli. Big wicket, nonetheless, and a very timely one

dismissalText.commentary: Ishant Sharma c †Wade b Marsh 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 0

commentTextItems.html: and that will be the game. Marsh takes the final wicket. 18 in succession at home for Australia. Full delivery outside off, a thick outside edge is easily taken by Wade. Australia go 4-0 up.

commentPostTextItems.html: 10.10pm This has been some match. This has been some turnaround from Australia. Australia go 4-0 up and extend their home streak to 18 ODIs. But that will not be the story of the day. India were cruising the chase with such ease that it looked like Australia had almost given up before Dhawan had cut a ball to Bailey at point. Ever since, it was all Australia. India failed to win an over as they stumbled and staggered to an unbelievable 25-run loss. A lot of credit has to be given to Shikhar Dhawan and Virat Kohli though, who made run-making look ridiculously simple. Splendid centuries but a real shame they could not carry on to take India home.

MS Dhoni: "Im not angry, I'm disappointed. This was one game we should have batted much better. I'll take responsibility, I should have carried on but I got out.. There was a bit of pressure on the youngsters. International cricket is all about pressure, you think about the right shot. You realise you have to take a bit more time and take the game slightly to the end. Rohit batted very well with Shikhar. And Dhawan and Kohli batted majestically. In the last five years, we have not had a fixed bowling line up other than the spinners. That pushes us to the extreme to get some extra runs.

Kane Richardson is the Man of the Match: "It's a funny old game, cricket. We always knew it would speed up once we got a wicket but we did not get it. Hastings could be up here as well. You try and bowl good balls but sometimes they go for sixes. Its our job to try and stop em.

Steven Smith: "It looked like they were cruising, a coupe, of wickets swing things. Richardson did very well as well. You have to try everything when Kohli and Shikhar Dhawan were batting, it felt like we needed 15 or 16 fielders. We had a never say die attitude tonight. When we had a sniff, we made a run for it.

commentTextItems.html: full and wide outside off, Ishant beaten
another slower ball outside off, the legcutter spins away from Jadeja and he is beaten. Ishant comes down but is sent back.
another slower legcutter that bounces extra outside off, Jadeja cannot get bat on it again
slower back of the hand legcutter outside off, Jadeja misses
wide yorker outside off, Jadeja gets some bat on his late deflection and the ball goes for four to third man
nudged to long-on for two. Played that with soft hands and was able to get back. Good batting that.
very wide outside off. Wide this time
full yorker outside off, smeared back
full and wide, left alone. Six events in that over
fullish on off, played down to the keeper

another drop. Wade has spilled another chance. Short outside off, Jadeja goes for a the cut but gets a thick outside edge, Wade leaps up high and drops yet another

commentPreTextItems.html: Rama: "the fall of dominoes! what a meltdown.. from majestic batting to downright medocrity.."

commentTextItems.html: Richardson drops a sitter. Should have been taken that. Full delivery and Yadav goes for another of his slogs. This one goes straight up. Richardson runs in from long-off and spills a relatively easy chance.

commentPreTextItems.html: Mitchell Marsh pulls up just before delivery stride and clutches his hamstring immediately. Is he cramping? He is in terrible pain at the moment. Seems to be a bit of cramp, because he is hanging around. Plenty of fluids being consumed. He is going to continue.

commentTextItems.html: full and wide outside off, another slog. Another miss
finally he gets bat on it, but all he will do is get one. Things just not happening for India. Slogged to deep midwicket

this is not clever slogging from Yadav. Doesn't keep his shape, or his eyes on the ball. Just goes after an almighty swing. Missed
length delivery on leg, Yadav is hustled for pace and is struck on the pad high up

dismissalComment.html: taken. Very good catch from Gurkeerat at fine leg. A nothing delivery on middle stump, Smith goes for the heave but gets a top edge which flies to fine leg. Goes very high in the air and hangs there for quite a while. Mann backtracks, comes forward, backtracks and takes it

dismissalText.long: c RG Sharma b I Sharma
dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey c RG Sharma b I Sharma 10 (7b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 142.85

dismissalComment.html: misses his length this time does Ishant but he gets a wicket. Full on middle, Bailey smashes it high in the air towards long-on, Rohit runs around and takes a good catch. Great over this, but 11 still come off it.

dismissalText.commentary: James Faulkner b Yadav 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: 'Finisher Faulkner' goes for a golden globe. Nice slower delivery on middle, Faulkner gets down to try and sweep but the ball keeps a touch low and sneaks through to rattle into the stumps.

dismissalText.commentary: Matthew Wade run out (RG Sharma/Yadav) 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gone. Wade is run out this time. Slower delivery outside off, played towards point. Maxi calls Wade through. Wade is a little slow to get off and pays for it with his wicket. Rohit returns the throw on the bounce, and Yadav backtracks to the wicket to take the bails off. Good work

headshotImage.caption: Manish Pandey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Manish Pandey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c sub (MK Pandey) b I Sharma
dismissalText.commentary: Glenn Maxwell c sub (MK Pandey) b I Sharma 41 (20b 6x4 1x6 29m) SR: 205

dismissalComment.html: what a catch from Pandey to finish. Just a sensational catch. Length on middle, Maxi pulls but doesn't get all if it again, his feet is parallel to the ground as he flies for the take. Great grab. But Maxwell has played a blinder

headshotImage.caption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma c †Wade b Richardson 41 (25b 2x4 3x6 28m) SR: 164

dismissalComment.html: gone. What a poor ball, but Rohit has to go. That is a real shame. Drifts down leg, and Rohit looks to flick but the ball kisses the glove. Wade scurries along and takes a lovely diving catch. Rohit's blitz ends.

headshotImage.caption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shikhar Dhawan c Bailey b Hastings 126 (113b 14x4 2x6 154m) SR: 111.5

dismissalComment.html: the misfield seems to have done Australia a favour. Can that change things? Or is too little too late? Dhawan goes. End of a scintillating knock from Dhawan. A smashing 126. A slower delivery outside off and Dhawan goes for the cut but cannot keep it down as backward point takes it.

headshotImage.caption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Smith b Richardson 106 (92b 11x4 1x6 131m) SR: 115.21

dismissalComment.html: Kohli finds the fielder. What is happening here? A nothing delivery from Richardson, fullish on leg. Kohli comes down the track and lobs a catch to mid-off. Just spooned up. Looked like a checked drive. Big big wicket. But, that has been a truly special innings from Kohli.

headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni c †Wade b Hastings 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Dhoni goes now. The crowd goes wild. Legcutter outside off, Dhoni comes down to try and manufacture a shot. He pokes at it and gets a thin outside edge which is gratefully accepted by Wade. Australia not out of it, just yet.

headshotImage.longCaption: Gurkeerat Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Gurkeerat Singh Mann c sub (SE Marsh) b Lyon 5 (6b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: taken by Shaun marsh. Gurkeerat persishes now. Flat on middle and leg, Gurkeerat goes for the big sweep but gets a top edge which goes very high in the air. Marsh circles around from square leg and takes a catch overhead. Pressure catch. Australia are right in it

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja not out 24 (27b 1x4 0x6 48m) SR: 88.88

headshotImage.caption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ajinkya Rahane c Smith b Richardson 2 (3b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: did that carry? Smith claims it. The slip fielder takes it. Smith put himself in there and takes a very good low catch. Full delivery outside off, Rahane tries to guide to third man but gets a thick outside edge. Smith takes it. Massive wicket. India are six down now.

headshotImage.caption: Rishi Dhawan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rishi Dhawan player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Rishi Dhawan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rishi Dhawan player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rishi Dhawan c Warner b Richardson 9 (8b 1x4 0x6 8m) SR: 112.5

dismissalComment.html: Dhawan has to go now, he has holed out to the sweeper cover. Full delivery, cross seam from Richardson outside off. Dhawan comes down the pitch to try and loft over cover but the ball skews off the outside half. Goes high in the air and Warner settles under it to take a good catch.

headshotImage.caption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Bhuvneshwar Kumar c Smith b Richardson 2 (6b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: taken now. Bhuvneshwar carves this with tentative hands and tentative feet to first slip. Smith makes no mistake.  A shortish delivery that outside off. Richardson has a five-for. What an astounding turnaround this.

dismissalText.commentary: Umesh Yadav c Bailey b Marsh 2 (11b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 18.18

dismissalComment.html: this time, Bailey intervenes and takes it. Fuller length on off, Yadav is not changing his technique, another wild slog. the ball goes up again, but nowhere near enough distance. Bailey, from point, has a look at Smith and then settles under it to pouch it.

dismissalText.commentary: Ishant Sharma c †Wade b Marsh 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: and that will be the game. Marsh takes the final wicket. 18 in succession at home for Australia. Full delivery outside off, a thick outside edge is easily taken by Wade. Australia go 4-0 up.
